  "body": "Follow up for https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/18055\r\n\r\n### Steps:\r\n1. Open an empty chat. (or clear the existing one)\r\n2. Send messages sequentially, one by one.\r\n3. Observe the behavior of the top bar.\r\n4. Scroll up within the chat.\r\n5. While at the top, send an additional message.\r\n\r\n### Actual result:\r\nThe top bar does not appear promptly after sending a message, particularly when the user is positioned at the top of the chat,\r\n\r\nOn IOS\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/78071f42-8733-4ac4-bf7f-00fab4132a89\r\n\r\nOn Android\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/f7aac4c2-4d0c-4721-8360-b6abe6d1d225\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected result:\r\nThe top bar should be shown when the 1-1 avatar is hidden\r\n\r\nHow it worked on the nightly [18 Dec 2023]\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/3d59d5e0-b02d-4fb7-88d7-6a76e053ce96\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Devices:\r\n- iPhone 11 Pro max, IOS 16\r\n- Pixel 7a. Android 14\r\n\r\n",
